msgid "Application Events"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:10
msgid ""
"The TestContext framework provides support for recording "
"xref:core/beans/context-introduction.adoc#context-functionality-events[application "
"events] published in the `ApplicationContext` so that assertions can be "
"performed against those events within tests. All events published during the "
"execution of a single test are made available via the `ApplicationEvents` "
"API which allows you to process the events as a `java.util.Stream`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:12
msgid "To use `ApplicationEvents` in your tests, do the following."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:15
msgid ""
"Ensure that your test class is annotated or meta-annotated with "
"xref:testing/annotations/integration-spring/annotation-recordapplicationevents.adoc[`@RecordApplicationEvents`]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Ensure that the `ApplicationEventsTestExecutionListener` is "
"registered. Note, however, that `ApplicationEventsTestExecutionListener` is "
"registered by default and only needs to be manually registered if you have "
"custom configuration via `@TestExecutionListeners` that does not include the "
"default listeners."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:23
msgid ""
"When using the "
"xref:testing/testcontext-framework/support-classes.adoc#testcontext-junit-jupiter-extension[SpringExtension "
"for JUnit Jupiter], declare a method parameter of type `ApplicationEvents` "
"in a `@Test`, `@BeforeEach`, or `@AfterEach` method."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:25
msgid ""
"Since `ApplicationEvents` is scoped to the lifecycle of the current test "
"method, this is the recommended approach."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:27
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can annotate a field of type `ApplicationEvents` with "
"`@Autowired` and use that instance of `ApplicationEvents` in your test and "
"lifecycle methods."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:32
msgid ""
"`ApplicationEvents` is registered with the `ApplicationContext` as a "
"_resolvable dependency_ which is scoped to the lifecycle of the current test "
"method. Consequently, `ApplicationEvents` cannot be accessed outside the "
"lifecycle of a test method and cannot be `@Autowired` into the constructor "
"of a test class."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/testing/testcontext-framework/application-events.adoc:36
msgid ""
"The following test class uses the `SpringExtension` for JUnit Jupiter and "
"{assertj-docs}[AssertJ] to assert the types of application events published "
"while invoking a method in a Spring-managed component:"
msgstr ""

